    "Specifically, these models typically strip the sequence-to-sequence head and replace it with a classification head to obtain a deterministic output to evaluate the model.",
    "The initial textual output head, which predicts the next textual token, is replaced by a classification head vector which has a dimension equivalent to the number of prediction classes, e.g two for a binary classification.",
    "Lira et al. [7] investigated the capabilities of LLMs such as GPT-3.5, GPT-4, and ADA to detect Distributed Denial of Service (DDoS) attacks on the CI-CIDS2017 [8] and Urban IoT [9] datasets.",
    "Their findings indicate that LLMs, when fine-tuned or employed in few-shot learning scenarios, could detect DDoS attacks with significant accuracy proving their adaptivity trait.",
    "Manocchio et al. [10] explored various encoding and classification methods on different transformer architectures, including GPT 's and BERT 's to enhance network analysis."
